Patch summary:
Store checkfc's getopt result in an int.
getopt() returns int and uses -1 as the end-of-options sentinel. ARM64 treats
plain char as unsigned, so storing that sentinel in char turns it into 255 and
the parser falls through to usage() after valid arguments. x86 hosts happen to
work because plain char is signed there.

diff --git a/tools/checkfc.c b/tools/checkfc.c
--- a/tools/checkfc.c
+++ b/tools/checkfc.c
@@ -384,7 +384,7 @@ int main(int argc, char **argv)
   bool allow_empty = false;
   bool compare = false;
   bool test_data = false;
-  char c;
+  int c;
 
   filemode mode = filemode_file_contexts;
 
